From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Armbian <build@armbian.com>
Date: Tue, 21 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] ufs: invalidate pdata after DMA like mainline

Radxa UFS only invalidates the SCSI data buffer before starting DMA.
Mainline flushes before and invalidates after ufshcd_send_command so
the CPU cannot observe stale cache lines for DATA-IN payloads.

Add the post-DMA invalidate for DMA_FROM_DEVICE transfers.

--- a/drivers/ufs/ufs.c	2026-07-21 17:29:38.546750097 +0200
+++ b/drivers/ufs/ufs.c	2026-07-21 17:29:38.610751697 +0200
@@ -1566,6 +1566,15 @@
 		goto retry;
 	}
 
+	/* Match mainline: drop stale cache lines after device DMA writeback. */
+	if (pccb->datalen && pccb->dma_dir == DMA_FROM_DEVICE) {
+		uintptr_t aaddr = (uintptr_t)pccb->pdata & ~(ARCH_DMA_MINALIGN - 1);
+
+		invalidate_dcache_range(aaddr,
+			ALIGN(aaddr + pccb->datalen + ARCH_DMA_MINALIGN - 1,
+			      ARCH_DMA_MINALIGN));
+	}
+
 	ocs = ufshcd_get_tr_ocs(hba);
 	switch (ocs) {
 	case OCS_SUCCESS:
